# Virtual Letter of Life (VLOL) Application 
## Description
 TBD

## Enviroment requirments
* Make
* Docker 

## Developer Guide

Run this this make command to create the Docker image (vlol-build-env) capable of building and testing
the VLOL application.
```
make build-env
```
```
WSLv2-MEGATRON@:~/GitHub/umgc.vlol.2$ make build-env
docker build -f ./docker/Dockerfile.build.env -t vlol-build-env:latest .
Sending build context to Docker daemon  93.98MB
Step 1/4 : FROM centos:latest
 ---> 0d120b6ccaa8
Step 2/4 : RUN yum install -y                     java-11-openjdk-devel          make                           wget
 ---> Using cache
 ---> 590a6ccb8aa0
Step 3/4 : RUN cd /var/tmp &&     wget http://www.gtlib.gatech.edu/pub/apache/maven/maven-3/3.6.3/binaries/apache-maven-3.6.3-bin.tar.gz &&     tar xf apache-maven-3.6.3-bin.tar.gz -C /usr/lib &&     ln -s /usr/lib/apache-maven-3.6.3/bin/mvn /usr/bin/mvn
 ---> Using cache
 ---> 486b44dc5599
Step 4/4 : ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/jre-11-openjdk-11.0.8.10-0.el8_2.x86_64
 ---> Using cache
 ---> ce827f0cb6a6
Successfully built ce827f0cb6a6
Successfully tagged vlol-build-env:latest
```


Run this command to start the vlol-build-env Docker image with the gitrepo mapped under /repo
Then run command as nessary
```
make start-env
```
```
WSLv2-MEGATRON@:~/GitHub/umgc.vlol.2$ make start-env
docker run -it -v /root/GitHub/umgc.vlol.2/:/repo vlol-build-env:latest bash
[root@069fa498aeca /]# cd repo/
[root@069fa498aeca repo]# ls
Makefile  README  azure-pipelines.yml  data.sql  docker  docs  nbactions.tmp  nbactions.xml  nbproject  pom.xml  qr_code_testpage.pdf  schema.sql  src  system.properties  target  vloldb.mv.db  vloldb.trace.db
[root@069fa498aeca repo]#
```

Run this command to build the VLOL application with in the vlol-build-env context
```
make all
```

Run this command to display make recipes and targets
```
make help
```
```
WSLv2-MEGATRON@:~/GitHub/umgc.vlol.2$ make help
        make all:
                This recipe starts the volo-build-env with repo volumed
                mapped into the container can creates the vlol-app jar
                then exits. This is useful so that developer do not
                need to modify enviorments.
        make vlol-app:
                This recipe creats the vlol java jar
        make build-env:
                This recipe create the Docker image capable of building
                the vlol-app
        make start-env:
                This recipe start the Docker image
        make clean:
                This recipe cleans the user workspace
                This recipe prints make commands
```